TY  - JOUR
AU  - Jarrow, Robert A.
T1  - Preferences, Continuity, and the Arbitrage Pricing Theory
PY  - 1988
Y1  - 1988/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/1.2.159
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 1
IS  - 2
SP  - 159
EP  - 172
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article investigates the structure on preferences required to derive Ross's arbitrage pricing theory (APT). It is shown that only ordinal preferences are required. In particular, the APT does not require that agents possess preferences representable as risk-averse expected utility functions. This characteristic of the APT is not shared by the standard equilibrium-based capital asset pricing models.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/1.2.159
ER  - 



